{
  "stem": "7414.7",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was so cold that, for example, we had to have water in the bucket, in the room where we lived.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the morning when I got up, I had to break the ice in the bucket with a axe now because it was-- everything was frozen stiff.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was such a cold winter.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And anyway, we stayed there and then the Russians started to advance.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as it was a German-populated area, all the peasant flew on the sign on that the Russians are coming, and we were left alone.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had nothing even to eat.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were a few rotten potatoes, a few rotten carrots in the cellar, and that was that and this time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were no peasant anymore where to-- even to get something.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this young couple decided when the Russian took over Lodz, they decided to go back home, and they begged me to go with them.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But then, I had a glimmer that when the Russian are here, perhaps I will be able to go back to Szczecin, somehow.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I told them, no, I will stay.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my uncle went to Warsaw to see what's happened there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I stayed all alone with the baby in this abandoned, lonely hut.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But then he came back, and he told me-- How long were you alone?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know, a few days.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was also rotten potatoes and rotten-- you should have seen the baby Michael.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He just closed his eyes when he saw it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was a good eater.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But anyway, he--",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
